President Obama released a statement regarding the resignation of CIA Director David Petraeus. He praised Petraeus for his extraordinary service to the United States, highlighting his leadership in adapting the military to new challenges and his role in bringing the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan to a responsible end. The President expressed confidence in the CIA's ability to continue its mission under Acting Director Michael Morell. He also extended his thoughts and prayers to Petraeus and his wife, Holly, and wished them the best during this difficult time.